lesson 15 i.grammar the structural particle and_the complement of state_a in chinese the so-called complement of_state is the one that describes or comments on the achieved state of an_action it is usually formed by an_adjective or an_adjectival phrase the particle is often used in such a_structure which must be placed between the_verb and_the complement of_state note its placement in the affirmative negative and_the a-not-v question forms she came very early he rest well how is spoken chinese note the first verb can_be omitted if there is an_object immediately after the verb does shanghai develop fast or not particle as an_indication of_confirming the completion realization of an_action the particle can_follow a_verb to denote the completion or realization of an_action which is usually placed at the end_of a_sentence when present the particle indicates that action has taken place in the past to negate_a sentence with the particle place the adverb rather than before the_verb and_omit from the end of_the sentence the following are some examples note its negative and a-not-v question forms went to_shanghai or have gone to_shanghai go to_shanghai or gone to_shanghai or or did you go to shanghai or have you gone to shanghai compare the sentences_with and_without an_action is going to take place vs an_action has taken place where are you going where have you been or where did you go what are you going to buy what have you bought or what did you buy reduplication of_the verb_a in chinese reduplicating verb has the functions_of implying short duration for that action and the idea of_giving something a_try similar to adding to the_verb here are some examples of_the reduplication of_the verb aa form take a_look have a_talk form take a_look wait a_second abab form make an_introduction get acquainted
